comment: The Principle of Transfinite Induction. Theorem 7.17 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 39. This principle states that if ` A ` is a class of ordinal numbers with the property that every ordinal number included in ` A ` also belongs to ` A ` , then every ordinal number is in ` A ` . See theorem ~ tfindes or ~ tfinds for the version involving basis and induction hypotheses. (Contributed by NM, 18-Feb-2004.)
